                  <bindingDesc resp="#BCBB">
                     <binding notAfter="1800" notBefore="1700">
                        <p>18th century, <placeName key="place_1000080">Italian</placeName>, probably bound for <persName>Jacopo Nani of San Trovaso (1724-1797)</persName>, <placeName key="place_7018159">Venice</placeName> 
                           and donated to the Biblioteca Marciana by the Nani family in 1797. The front paste-down has the Nani bookplate, bearing the arms, party per bend or and gules beneath a coronet.
                           Pasteboards; shiny brown leather, speckled with black dots; no decoration on covers; spine fully gilt, 
                           no original title, later paper label(s); edges gilt, only partially gauffered (after severe trimming of text-block); paste-downs of marbled paper. The manuscript had been damaged at both ends before this binding</p>
                     </binding>
                     
